oai_dc:dc.dc:description:
We consider spherical principal series representations of the semisimple Lie group of rank one $G=SO(n, 1; \mathbb K)$, $\mathbb K= r,  c,  h$. There is a family of unitarizable representations $\pi_{
u}$ of $G$ for $
u$ in an interval on $\mathbb R^+$, the so-called complementary series, and subquotient or subrepresentations of $G$ for $
u$ being negative integers. We consider the restriction of $(\pi_{
u}, G)$ under the subgroup $H=SO(n-1, 1; \mathbb K)$. We prove the appearing of discrete components. The corresponding results for the exceptional Lie group $F_{4(-20)}$ and its subgroup $Spin(8,1)$ are also obtained.

Comment: 8 pages, 4 figures, submitted to Proc. IAU Symp. 287 "Cosmic masers -
  from OH to H_0", R.S. Booth, E.M.L. Humphreys, W.H.T. Vlemmings (eds.),
  invited paper

