oai_dc:dc.dc:description:
The lower bound usually cited for Poisson's ratio {
u} is -1, derived from the relationship between {
u} and the bulk and shear moduli. From consideration of the longitudinal and biaxial moduli, we recently determined that the lower bound on {
u} for isotropic materials is actually 1/5, a value also consistent with experimental measurements on real materials. Herein we generalize this result, first by analyzing expressions for {
u} in terms of six common elastic constants, and then by considering arbitrary strains. The results corroborate the prior finding that 1/5 <= {
u} for linear elasticity to be applicable.
